 |RKBDarkwind PK Overview
|WKB~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
|BKB-  |GKBDarkwind has a fairly simple PK (player killer) system.

|BKB-  |GKBOnce a player registers as a PKer, returning to non-PK status is possible
   with some very stiff penalties. Becoming a PKer is a decision that should
   not be taken lightly.

|BKB-  |GKBA player must register PK before level 30 to do so without penalty. If a
   player registers after level 29, they will be subject to loss of
   levels and stats dropping the player to level 20. This includes
   those that have attained the maximum level of 250.

|BKB-  |GKBBalance of skills between guilds will not encompass PK.
   Balance issues will strictly be considered by the admin for
   the benefit of the mud as a whole. Complaints such as a hold
   spell lasting too long, or poison doing too much damage in
   PK, will not be addressed since they are in balance for
   general combat. In PK, you must plan around these shortcomings.
   Only bugs in skills will be addressed for PK purposes.

|BKB-  |GKBRegistering and unregistering PK is done two west and two south of the
   center of Darkwind city.

|BKB-  |GKBIt is possible to unregister PK if you've gone an appropriate amount of
   playing time without PK activity. Visit the PK Registration room for more
   information.

|BKB-  |GKBAnyone that is registered as PK can kill anyone else that is
   registered. 

|WKB~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 |RKBDarkwind PK Rules
|WKB~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

|BKB1. |CKBIn PK to PK combat, no non-PK interference is allowed - period.
   This means no healing of PK players during PK combat, no locates,
   no clearminds, no supplying food or drink in any form - not even
   in the moments after combat has ended. If a considerable amount
   of time has passed since the PK interaction, and the player
   requests a heal, clearmind, or other type of assistance, then
   this is acceptable. If you are worried you are toeing this line,
   don't take the risk as the penalty for violation of this rule is
   the loss of five levels, and five stats from each stat category
   and you will be force-regged PK.

|BKB2. |CKBDo not post anything concerning issues you have with PK to any
   boards. If a player violates the rules of PK, send a mudmail
   with a log of the incident to the administration of Darkwind (IMP+), 
   and if the rules have been violated, penalties will be enforced 
   accordingly. Corresponding emails from witnesses will help your cause, 
   as we all know logs have been known to be fabricated. Failure to adhere
   to this rule will result in a loss of one level, and one stat
   from each stat category.

   |BKB2a) |CKBDo not use shout, gossip, or other public channels for pk related
       chatting. The newbie channel may be used to inform newbies on the
       nature of PK on DarkWind.

|BKB3.|CKB No complaints will be accepted in the violation of these rules if
   they are accompanied by complaining, or insulting tones towards the
   administration of Darkwind. What this means is, proofread what you 
   write before you mudmail the administration about an incident, state
   only the facts and no opinions. The situation will be handled in as
   timely a fashion as possible. If your mudmail is in violation of
   these rules, you will lose one level, and one stat from each stat
   category.

|BKB4.|CKB Deliberate repeated abuse of a bug in PK will result in the
   demotion of your character to level 1, with 1 in each stat, while
   maintaining your current PK status. Banishment will also be
   considered, all the way up to a site ban. What constitutes bug
   abuse is totally at the discretion of the Darkwind administration,
   so if you are not sure if it is a bug or not, don't do it. Report
   it to the administration via mudmail, adhering to rule 3.

|BKB5.|CKB If we all follow these simple rules PK should run more smoothly
   than it has in the past on Darkwind. Please help us keep things
   under control, so PK can remain a part of Darkwind.

|BKB6. |CKBYou cannot deliberately resurrect a player (in any way) to immediately
   PK that person again, in order to get guaranteed contiguous kills. If
   caught, this will result in an immediate punishing of both the resurrecting
   player and the killing player.
   
|BKB7. |CKBStacking mobs -- If a player chooses to stack mobs from
   an area. They must NOT leave aggro monsters for other players
   to wander into. This is considered as unsanctioned PKing. Any
   player caught doing this and/or it causes the death of another
   player, the offensing player will face the loss of 5 levels, 5
   from all stat categories (including meta), and will be force-regged
   PK. Dragons found in violation of this will also lose 5 from their
   age. Additional punishments will happen with each violation, up
   to and including banishment from creating mythic characters,
   purging, and total banishment.

